message_1: Find all prime numbers between 50 and 70 (inclusive).
message_2:
To find all prime numbers between 50 and 70 (inclusive), we will check each number in this range to see if it is divisible by any number other than 1 and itself. If it is not, then it is a prime number.

Here are the prime numbers between 50 and 70:

53: Prime (only divisible by 1 and 53)
59: Prime (only divisible by 1 and 59)
61: Prime (only divisible by 1 and 61)
67: Prime (only divisible by 1 and 67)

So, the prime numbers between 50 and 70 (inclusive) are 53, 59, 61, and 67.
